result.formatted_address: 41 Connaught Rd Central, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Ying Jee Club

reviews.text:
Classy setting, exceptional service and refined food.

Pricing is on the higher end though and while everything was of high standard from the ambience, table setting, cutlery, friendly service and the quality of the food, there wasn't any dishes that really stood out with a wow factor.

It's a pleasant experience nonetheless.

The food is great, the service is good (not always great), the environment is okay.

I don't think it's worth the price - at least the tasting menu isn't.
Took my clients there for lunch.. We ordered the lunch menu (~$690 per pax).  Food was okay, but wasn’t like WOW.   Still will go again with guests and clients because of their attentive service.
Ying Jee Club is great and the standard of food is always at the highest but be prepared to dig deep into your wallet
Tried both lunch and dinner, creative and very solid dim sum. Dinner is also excellent with very good food and service. Not a frugal place but worth the price of admission.
